# Database Safety ‚Äî NEVER Run migrate:fresh Directly

## Critical

**NEVER run `migrate:fresh` or `migrate:fresh --env=testing` directly.**  
Without `.env.testing`, `--env=testing` does NOT switch databases ‚Äî the main DB (from .env) is used and will be destroyed.

## Test vs Dev Database (Isolation)

- **Main/Dev DB:** `laravel` (from .env) ‚Äî your real data
- **Test DB:** `testing` ‚Äî Sail creates this on MySQL init; tests and `--env=testing` use it

`.env.testing` sets `DB_DATABASE=testing` so tests and any `--env=testing` command never touch `laravel`.

## Safe Test DB Refresh

To refresh only the testing database:

```bash
./scripts/test-db-fresh.sh
# or
composer test:db-fresh
```

## Running Tests

```bash
./vendor/bin/sail test
# or
./vendor/bin/sail exec laravel.test php artisan test
```

Tests use `DB_DATABASE=testing` (phpunit.xml + .env.testing). Your `laravel` database is never modified.

## Main Database

For the main/development database, use `migrate` (not migrate:fresh) unless the user explicitly requests a full reset.
